eds some visa \nto go there if she is=C2=\r\n=A0not the Creater.=C2=A0As you say all higher deity are \nthere but less in=\r\n ability. Does the deities have even less =C2=A0ability on \nearth plane.&gt;&gt;\n=\r\n\nShe needs no visa, but neither does She interfere without a genuine cause =\r\nor a genuine call. Everything is Her world, then why is there ugliness, cri=\r\nme, evil things? Who creates the Asuras, if not She? And it is She herself =\r\nwho gave them the liberty to act as per their freewill. This world is a pla=\r\ny of forces and a democracy of opportunities. Every impulse, however Divine=\r\n or anti-Divine in aim, is given a chance to run its course and actualize i=\r\ntself in the Universe. THAT is Her Divine Compassion! That is why She is TH=\r\nE GREATEST Mother. She is mother to the Great Gods as much to the Danavas a=\r\nnd Daityas, and Rakshasas and Bhutas and Pretas and other corrupt human bei=\r\nng and what not. \n\nNow coming to your question on the phrase &quot;higher deitie=\r\ns having less ability&quot;. I think I have not been able to explain clearly, si=\r\nnce in the last mail I was merely writing in the context of that discussion=\r\n. Let me try here.\n\nThere are three basic layer of this Universe. The physi=\r\ncal, the astral or subtle layer, and the causal (karana jagat) layer. In th=\r\nis subtle layer, which lies superimposed on our own physical plane, there i=\r\ns a whole wide world of all possible forces, just like in our own world. It=\r\n is a layer which is created out of force of pranashakti. This force of pra=\r\nnashakti in humans beings is what causes all emotive movements on the consc=\r\niousness - joy, happiness, love, passion, rage, fear, anger, hatred, disgus=\r\nt, lust, attachments etc etc. These are also capable of influencing the thi=\r\nnking mind is us. Now the core philosophy of sadhana and specially Tantrik =\r\nsadhana, is to create a formation of the deity using ones own prana-shakti =\r\nthrough the aid of repeated rituals and procedures and mantras etc. If you =\r\nthink carefully, you will realize that every idol, ever homa agni needs a p=\r\nranapratisthapana ritual before starting. The sadhaka used the force of his=\r\n/her own\n pranashakti to infuse life into a subtle formation of the deity. =\r\nOnce this process is successfully done, this sublte formation of the deity =\r\nwhich exists in the subtle plane, has a life of its own. It can then guide =\r\nthe sadhaka through the path and eventually, one day lead him/her to the re=\r\nal abode of the deity which is the karana-jagat (beyond this astral plane).=\r\n If a person is able to awaken his/her Kundalini shakti, and make it identi=\r\nfy/create such an astral formation of the deity, it becomes an even more po=\r\nwerful force. It is, from our limited human perspective, as much a powerful=\r\n entity as we may imagine, yet it is often not the actual Deity yet. Exactl=\r\ny the same thing has been described by Sri Vimalananda in the Aghora books,=\r\n if you read carefully.=C2=A0 \n\nWhen a sadhaka has been able to associate w=\r\nith such an astral formation of the deity, it can guide the sadhaka along t=\r\nhe path provided the sadhaka also is trying to work hard and sincerely to r=\r\neach the causal planes (the real spiritual planes of existence where the re=\r\nal force of the Deity originates). The difference, if you ask, between this=\r\n astral formation of the deity and the real deity is that, the former is ne=\r\nither bound nor capable by itself of causing a complete and total transform=\r\nation of the average human nature without a proactive help of the sadhaka. =\r\nWhereas, if one reaches the plane of the Great Gods, which is where the rea=\r\nl deity exists, one cannot avoid being transformed in mind, emotions, body =\r\netc. And what kind of a transformation will it be? One that will reflect to=\r\n the world as a greater and genuine humility, sense of deep surrender to th=\r\ne Divine at ALL time and unfailingly, a complete withdrawal of lower nature=\r\n of man - lust, anger,\n jealousy, greed, covetousness - an abiding peace, c=\r\nalm, detachment, mental-illumination, genuine compassion, a widening of the=\r\n consciousness. Such an individual, even if he/she just sits down next to a=\r\nnother person, will exude a silent strong peace and unselfish love which wi=\r\nll automatically calm the minds and disturbed emotions of lesser mortals ET=\r\nC. THAT is the authentic, unhindered flow of the Divine Power of any of the=\r\n great deities. This comes even if one deity is properly realized in the ca=\r\nusal planes of existence. But the astral formation of the same deity, which=\r\n is created by the force of our own pranashakti or Kundalini as the case ma=\r\nybe, is often not capable of affecting this kind of a total transformation =\r\nin a sadhaka. That is why it is limited. It is not limited because it can&#39;t=\r\n=C2=A0 get me a better job or a nice pay hike or cure some diseases or brin=\r\ng me fame or any such material benefit if I so ask of it - the astral forma=\r\ntions of the deities\n can very easily do all these things in the physical w=\r\norld - but it is limited because it cannot by itself give you the must auth=\r\nentic and persistent spirituality of the higher planes, the one aim and des=\r\ntination of all genuine sadhana.\n\nSince this astral plane is the way it is,=\r\n therefore it&#39;s extremely important to keep actively working on ourselves t=\r\no increase detachment, objectivity, genuine internal surrender (when that h=\r\nappens one accepts all life-situations without the slightest grudge), humil=\r\nity, control of anger, lust, jealousy etc. (all that is universally accepte=\r\nd as spiritual qualities). For unless these changes are affected at least t=\r\no some degree in the mind and emotions of the sadhaka, one is simply not re=\r\nady to reach the higher planes of God and benefit from them spiritually. Mo=\r\nreover, at every stage of spiritual evolution there is a gap between experi=\r\nence and realization. Only repeated experiences *may* lead to realization. =\r\nOne off experiences create a force no doubt, but in time it fritters away, =\r\nor worst, gets distorted by the impurities and conditioning of the sadhaka.=\r\n\n\n&lt;&lt;I am sure this is not your \ntheory. You have taken it from yogi Aurobin=\r\ndo. Many times when certain \nperson reach a stage in their spiritual path, =\r\nothers think whatever this guy is uttering is=C2=A0complete truth, when in =\r\nfact it is=C2=A0far from truth. \nOnce=C2=A0I saw in a article that Aurobind=\r\no said that Divine Lord who spoke \nGita completely forgot it after few minu=\r\ntes or so. I could not believe \nwhat I was reading. Then my respect for thi=\r\ns yogi went down the drain.&gt;&gt;\n\nYou surety is incorrect. There were certain =\r\nevents which happened in the last one and half years which made me sit down=\r\n and rethink my own understanding of spirituality. At about the same time I=\r\n started worshiping a specific personality of the Divine Mother, and the mo=\r\nre I meditated on Her, the more would thoughts pour into my mind that my un=\r\nderstanding of spirituality is imperfect and has serious flaws. I tried, us=\r\ning my own meditations to find out what was wrong or rather imperfectly und=\r\nerstood, what needed rethinking. First question I asked myself was, what is=\r\n the aim of spirituality? My mind could grasp some outlines of certain answ=\r\ners and processes and truths. But it was still not exceptionally clear.\n\nI =\r\nhad first read Sri Aurobindo when I was in college. I could not go beyond t=\r\nhe first two pages. They were bouncers going one mile over my head. Three y=\r\nears ago someone gave me a book of Sri Aurobindo. I could understand say 10=\r\n percent, and rest I rejected, partly due to ignorance and partly due to eg=\r\noistic arrogance. Never opened any of his writing since then. This year, as=\r\n my sadhana was going on and as I was instinctively trying to correct the f=\r\nlaws in my understanding, one day while meditating I had an inner thought i=\r\nn the form of an image, which told me that I should start reading Sri Aurob=\r\nindo but in a very specific manner. The image was very clear in my inner-ey=\r\ne, and thoroughly pressing on my consciousness. I opened his book again, an=\r\nd read it in the prescribed manner and this time it made a LOT of sense to =\r\nme. What I was struggling to understand all this year, whose outline I coul=\r\nd grasp yet not get a proper hang of, I was able to understand\n from his wr=\r\nitings with much deeper clarity.=C2=A0 Many of my own experiences made more=\r\n sense to me. Many sentences of Aghora books too made amply sense in a new =\r\nlight. I read 40 - 45 % of his writings. Then something in me told me to st=\r\nop at a certain point of his writings, for digesting the rest of the 60 % I=\r\n will have to first make more spiritual progress. Otherwise the rational mi=\r\nnd will distort the information. So I stopped. He whom I had rejected firml=\r\ny 3 years ago, now came back to sit on my consciousness like a blazing sun.=\r\n \n\nThe line that you mention, is from one of the earlier writings of Sri Au=\r\nrobindo on the historical problem of the Mahabharta. In the Mahabharata, th=\r\nere is an incident which comes later on, after the great war and when Yudhi=\r\nsthira was ruling the kingdom happily, when Arjuna asks Sri Krishna to repe=\r\nat the words he had spoken at the beginning of the war (The Gita) once more=\r\n since he has forgotten them, and Sri Krishna says, the time has passed awa=\r\ny (it was a special time when the Gita was spoken), he cannot repeat the &quot;e=\r\nxact words&quot; once again. \n\nSri Krishna was the main Guru of Aurobindo. Even =\r\nSwami Vivekananda was one of his Gurus, for during the time when Sri Aurobi=\r\nndo was in jail, for 15 days Swami Vivekananda would appear before him dail=\r\ny and instruct him on the various layers of the mind, which he was not awar=\r\ne of till then. Swami Vivekananda had already left his physical body by the=\r\nn. It was in the writings of Sri Aurobindo that he mentioned about the left=\r\n and right hemisphere of the brain and their difference in functionality, a=\r\nnd their connection to spirituality, about 30 years before medical science =\r\nconfirmed the same. \n\nRight from getting out of jail, to settling in Pondic=\r\nherry, to pushing his own spiritual experiences further into states of Saha=\r\nja (which he describes in different terminology), etc etc, he was guided co=\r\nntinuously by the Adesha of Sri Krishna. He would literally hear the voice =\r\nof Krishna speaking to him, instructing him to do this or do that. Krishna =\r\nwas his Guru, the Divine Mother beyond all manifestation, was his destinati=\r\non. Anyway, my point is not to try and sell Sri Aurobindo&#39;s perspective of =\r\nspirituality. I have benefited from it, but not necessary that everyone els=\r\ne will also benefit. There are so many sadgurus who have come to India, eac=\r\nh with their unique perspectives and ideas and philosophies. Each must indi=\r\nvidually try and find whose ideas gel properly with our mental and emotiona=\r\nl makeup, and help us to progress on the path. \n\nThough I now have a very d=\r\neep respect for Sri Aurobindo, I maintain a safe distance from both his cri=\r\ntics and his blind-admirers. Both of them, in my opinion, have misunderstoo=\r\nd the depth of his teachings. Both their love and their hatred is a functio=\r\nn of their own egos, like it was mine 3 years ago, and not based on any gen=\r\nuine understanding or appreciation. In spirituality, no Sadguru can be unde=\r\nrstood accurately or even slightly without sincere sadhana.\n\n\n&lt;&lt;\nDisclaimer=\r\n---- My thinking is \nvery different due to Darshan and=C2=A0Grace of Divine=\r\n Mother & Divine \nLord. Nobody should feel unhappy If I do not agree or fol=\r\nlow the \nleader.Thanks.&gt;&gt;\n\nI at-least will never feel unhappy if you disagr=\r\nee. There are \nmany saints, many philosophies, many paths, not everyone is =\r\nbound to \nlike every path.=C2=A0 Disagreement is perfectly ok. Because some=\r\none \ndisagrees with me or those whom I agree with, does not mean I like him=\r\n \nany less. I try to keep my=C2=A0 emotional side (where respect, love, \ndi=\r\nslike, hatred, anger, passions exist) separate from my thinking mind. \nIt i=\r\ns very much possible, through practice, for a man to disassociate \nhis rati=\r\nonal-mind from the emotional-mind. So have no fears that your \ndisagreement=\r\n is going to make me like you any less or any more.\n\nThe problem with the e=\r\nmotional part of our being is that it jumps up at appearances, running ahea=\r\nd to grasp the truth rather than waiting patiently for the truth to arrive =\r\nin all its aspects and dimensions, and in the process it distorts the truth=\r\n and then reacts to that distorted image. For example, recently in some soc=\r\nial forums I posted a comment that I found the Tantrik Adwaitha far more ap=\r\npealing than Sri Adi Shankara&#39;s Adwaitha, though the Adwaitha of Adi Shanka=\r\nra has many hard-selling supporters. Immediately some friends of mine on Tw=\r\nitter and otherwise, jumped to the false conclusion that I have disrespecte=\r\nd Adi Shankara, and tried best to make me &quot;see the truth&quot; by such grandiose=\r\n statements that=C2=A0 Shankara is the &#39;final word&#39; on Adwaitha and everyth=\r\ning else must be necessarily lesser. Or that I was making an egoistic denou=\r\nncement. Both of which are million light-years away from the truth. That Sr=\r\ni Adi Shankara was a special Vibhuti\n (manifestation) of God, that much I a=\r\nm certain. His compositions are so brilliant that it can&#39;t be sufficiently =\r\nappreciated in words. Yet, I have equally no qualms in rejecting his philos=\r\nophy. And because I am not bound to accept his philosophy, does not mean I =\r\nrespect or love him any less than any other great saint.=C2=A0\n\nIf you disr=\r\nespect a man, and specially a saint, and then start disliking him too with =\r\na passion, you are creating strong negative karmas. But if you can disagree=\r\n with someone without losing respect or love for the person, in an objectiv=\r\ne manner, you reap very little karmic effects. That is why Lord Krishna too=\r\n advices us to become more detached in life.\n\nIn conclusion, Narasimha is t=\r\notally correct. Many things cannot be sufficiently expressed in words witho=\r\nut causing some distortion.\n\n-Regards\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n=C2=A0\n\nawaktam wyakt=\r\nimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam=\r\n ||[7:24]\n\n\n________________________________\n From: Laxmi Narayan &lt;shrijish=\r\nrihari@...&gt;\nTo: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic-wisdom@yahoog=\r\nroups.com&gt; \nSent: Thursday, 11 October 2012 12:21 AM\nSubject: Re: [vedic-wi=\r\nsdom] Re: A thought\n \n\n=C2=A0 \n\n\n=C2=A0 \nDear Rajarshi Bhai,\nHow are you do=\r\ning? About 200 hundred years ago, a man made a theory of creation in France=\r\n. When Napolean asked where is God in it, the guy said, do not talk about G=\r\nod. It makes things complicated.\nSo is there a place for Divine Mother and =\r\nHer Love or Grace or Protection in your theory. Is=C2=A0this intermediate z=\r\none as you say is created by Her and part of Her creation=C2=A0or by=C2=A0s=\r\nomebody else.=C2=A0 Does=C2=A0She needs some visa to go there if she is=C2=\r\n=A0not the Creater.=C2=A0As you say all higher deity are there but less in =\r\nability. Does the deities have even less =C2=A0ability on earth plane.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nI am sure this is not your theory. You have taken it from yogi Aurobind=\r\no. Many times when certain person reach a stage in their spiritual path, ot=\r\nhers think